<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,716,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
T y p e m a t e r i a l 1, 
<specimenCount box="[475,592,748,768]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">1 syntypes</specimenCount>
(male 
<typeStatus box="[662,741,748,768]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">lectotype</typeStatus>
and female 
<typeStatus box="[864,980,748,768]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">paralectotype</typeStatus>
by present designation), well preserved; male bears label &quot;Touchètie&quot; [handwritten], and the female – label &quot;Grusia 1870&quot; [handwritten]. Close to both specimens, the following handwritten label is pinned on the bottom of box: &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="MOTSCH. Caucase Motschulsky" authorityName="MOTSCH. Caucase Motschulsky" box="[405,783,820,840]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stomoides">
<emphasis box="[405,492,820,840]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">stomoides</emphasis>
MOTSCH. Caucase Motschulsky
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (MNHN, &quot;Collection Chaudoir&quot;, box no 216 &quot; 
<emphasis box="[335,403,844,864]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Argutor</emphasis>
&quot;).
</paragraph>
