<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="663" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,716,896]" box="[178,1082,876,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
T y p e l o c a l i t y.&quot;AlpesdelaTouchétie(Caucasecentraletoriental)&quot;(
<bibRefCitation author="CHAUDOIR M" box="[877,1071,876,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" pagination="219 - 260" refId="ref4258" refString="CHAUDOIR M. de (1868): Description d'especes nouvelles ou peu connues de Feronia d'Europe et du bassin mediterraneen. - L'Abeille, Memoires d'Entomologie 5: 219 - 260." type="journal article" year="1868">CHAUDOIR 1868: 251</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,910,1103]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
M a l e g e n i t a l i a. Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[875,948,910,932]" captionStart="Figs 11-14" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1246,1266]" captionTargetBox="[200,1074,225,1217]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[178,1085,220,1236]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 11-14: Feronia stomoides CHAUDOIR, lectotype: Fig. (11) aedeagus, left lateral view; Fig. (12) apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; Fig. (13) right paramere, internal view; Fig. (14) right paramere, external view. Scale bar 0.5 mm (11-14)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5332866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5332866/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with ostium deflected to left, apical part longer than basal part and with straight ventral margin, tip of apex somewhat bent upwards; basal part with strongly developed and prominent ventral process; internal sac (inverted state) with single strongly chitinised piece. Apex of median lobe in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[446,521,1024,1046]" captionStart="Figs 11-14" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1246,1266]" captionTargetBox="[200,1074,225,1217]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[178,1085,220,1236]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 11-14: Feronia stomoides CHAUDOIR, lectotype: Fig. (11) aedeagus, left lateral view; Fig. (12) apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; Fig. (13) right paramere, internal view; Fig. (14) right paramere, external view. Scale bar 0.5 mm (11-14)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5332866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5332866/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) with tip deflected to left. Left paramere (
<figureCitation box="[964,1077,1024,1046]" captionStart="Figs 11-14" captionStartId="10.[178,218,1246,1266]" captionTargetBox="[200,1074,225,1217]" captionTargetId="figure-2@10.[178,1085,220,1236]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 11-14: Feronia stomoides CHAUDOIR, lectotype: Fig. (11) aedeagus, left lateral view; Fig. (12) apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; Fig. (13) right paramere, internal view; Fig. (14) right paramere, external view. Scale bar 0.5 mm (11-14)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5332866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5332866/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Figs 13-14</figureCitation>
) sickle-shaped, regularly round in middle; basal part forming big widened bulb; apical part with round (not pointed) tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1085,1117,1168]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
After drawing, the genitalia were included in Euparal and put on separate transparent label pinned under the 
<typeStatus box="[410,506,1146,1168]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1085,1182,1375]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
T a x o n o m i c n o t e s a n d r e l a t i o n s h i p s The presence of pubescence on the distal part of third antennomeres, dense and continuous punctuation on the basal part of pronotum, absence of medial setiferous punctures on hind coxae, glabrous ventral side of onychium, and sickle-shaped left paramere demonstrate that this species belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="JACOBSON" authorityYear="1907" box="[395,537,1296,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Oreoplatysma">
<emphasis box="[395,537,1296,1318]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Oreoplatysma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and not to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="CHAUDOIR" authorityYear="1838" box="[663,754,1296,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="666" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cryobius">
<emphasis box="[663,754,1296,1318]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Cryobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the following transfer is proposed: 
<taxonomicName authority="(CHAUDOIR 1868)" baseAuthorityName="CHAUDOIR" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[349,949,1324,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stomoides" subGenus="Oreoplatysma">
<emphasis box="[349,475,1324,1346]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Pterostichus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[492,635,1324,1346]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Oreoplatysma</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[652,753,1324,1346]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">stomoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CHAUDOIR M" box="[770,942,1324,1346]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" pagination="219 - 260" refId="ref4258" refString="CHAUDOIR M. de (1868): Description d'especes nouvelles ou peu connues de Feronia d'Europe et du bassin mediterraneen. - L'Abeille, Memoires d'Entomologie 5: 219 - 260." type="journal article" year="1868">CHAUDOIR 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, new assignment of 
<taxonomicName authority="(CHAUDOIR 1868)" baseAuthorityName="CHAUDOIR" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[262,804,1353,1375]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stomoides" subGenus="Cryobius">
<emphasis box="[262,388,1353,1375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Pterostichus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[403,495,1353,1375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">Cryobius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[511,612,1353,1375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">stomoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CHAUDOIR M" box="[625,797,1353,1375]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" pagination="219 - 260" refId="ref4258" refString="CHAUDOIR M. de (1868): Description d'especes nouvelles ou peu connues de Feronia d'Europe et du bassin mediterraneen. - L'Abeille, Memoires d'Entomologie 5: 219 - 260." type="journal article" year="1868">CHAUDOIR 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,1389,1525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
According to the external morphology and structure of the male genitalia, this species seems closer to the taxa from the group &quot; 
<emphasis box="[607,733,1418,1440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">daghestanus</emphasis>
&quot;, and especially to 
<taxonomicName authority="REITTER 1896" authorityName="REITTER" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chefsuricus">
<emphasis box="[942,956,1419,1440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[970,1085,1418,1440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">chefsuricus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="REITTER E" box="[178,329,1446,1468]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" pagination="211 - 215" refId="ref4942" refString="REITTER E. (1896): Ubersicht der mit Pterostichus pulchellus FALDERM. verwandten Coleopteren-Arten, = Agnodemus CHAUD. - Entomologische Nachrichten (Berlin) 22: 211 - 215." type="journal article" year="1896">REITTER 1896</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="KRYZHANOVSKIJ 1988" authorityName="KRYZHANOVSKIJ" authorityYear="1988" box="[395,824,1446,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirschenblatti">
<emphasis box="[395,410,1447,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[431,570,1446,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">kirschenblatti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KRYZHANOVSKIJ O" box="[585,824,1446,1468]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" pagination="12 - 21" refId="ref4660" refString="KRYZHANOVSKIJ O. L. (1988): [A review of the Caucasian species of the subgenus Oreoplatysma JACOBSON, 1906 (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Pterostichus)]. - Trudy Vsesoiuznogo Entomologichesjogo Obshchestva 70: 12 - 21 [in Russian]." type="journal article" year="1988">KRYZHANOVSKIJ 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the apex of aedeagus distinctly bent to left and somewhat turn upwards and different shape of the left paramere suppose that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="CHAUDOIR" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[410,540,1503,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stomoides">
<emphasis box="[410,425,1504,1525]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[439,540,1503,1525]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">stomoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from the other two species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,658,1540,1563]" box="[178,658,1540,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="CHAUDOIR" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[178,307,1540,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stomoides">
<emphasis box="[178,193,1542,1563]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[206,307,1540,1562]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">stomoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,861,1578,1600]" box="[178,861,1578,1600]" pageId="4" pageNumber="663">D i s t r i b u t i o n.Tushetia(KRYZHANOVSKIJ et al. 1995: 102).</paragraph>
